cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.MM

This paper is about whole brain segmentation using deep convolutional neural network (DCNN) segmentation methods, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of multi-atlas segmentation, which is a common method in medical image analysis and falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of clinically acquired MRI scans, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of coefficient of variation (CV) as a metric for reproducibility, which is commonly used in neural network evaluation and falls under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
